<db:section xml:id="StyleOptionType-enum">
<db:title>enum QStyleOptionSizeGrip::StyleOptionType</db:title>
<db:para>This enum is used to hold information about the type of the style option, and is defined for each <db:link xlink:href="qstyleoption.xml">QStyleOption</db:link> subclass.</db:para>
<db:informaltable>
<db:thead>
<db:tr>
<db:th>Constant</db:th>
<db:th>Value</db:th>
<db:th>Description</db:th>
</db:tr>
</db:thead>
<db:tr>
<db:td>
<db:para><db:code><db:emphasis role="bold"><db:link xlink:href="qstyleoptionsizegrip.xml">QStyleOptionSizeGrip</db:link></db:emphasis>::Type</db:code></db:para>
</db:td>
<db:td><db:code>SO_SizeGrip</db:code></db:td>
<db:td>
<db:para>The type of style option provided (<db:link xlink:href="qstyleoption.xml#OptionType-enum">SO_TabBarBase</db:link> for this class).</db:para>
</db:td>
</db:tr>
</db:informaltable>
<db:para>The type is used internally by <db:link xlink:href="qstyleoption.xml">QStyleOption</db:link>, its subclasses, and qstyleoption_cast() to determine the type of style option. In general you do not need to worry about this unless you want to create your own <db:link xlink:href="qstyleoption.xml">QStyleOption</db:link> subclass and your own styles.</db:para>
